[{"id":"VR876692","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two different uniform strings of the same length attached to each other forming a horizontal length. The string on the left has a smaller diameter than the string on the right. A small peak is shown on the left string and is moving to the right, toward the attachment point between the two strings.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876692.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two different uniform strings are attached to each other, as shown in the figure. The strings are made of the same material, and the string on the left has a smaller diameter than the string on the right. A wave pulse in the left string has an upward displacement and is traveling to the right, as indicated, toward the attachment point between the two strings. Which of the following correctly identifies the displacement direction for the wave pulse reflected back to the left at the point of attachment, and also correctly identifies whether a wave pulse is transmitted along the thick string on the right?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:30\"/><col class=\"colspec align:left colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:125\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:100\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Reflected Wave<span class=\"formatted_line_break delivery_mode:Both\"></span>Pulse Displacement</th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Is There a Transmitted <span class=\"formatted_line_break delivery_mode:Both\"></span>Wave Pulse?</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Remains upward</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Yes</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Remains upward</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">No</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Inverts to be downward</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Yes</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Inverts to be downward</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">No</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR876692_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":2}]